# Dense session handoff

When invoked (@-mention or user asks for **handoff** / **dense context** / **session summary for paste**), output **one** fenced or plain block they can copy into a new session—**no** long intro/outro.

Use terse labels; skip empty sections.

- **G** — goal (one line).
- **✓** — done (commits, paths, decisions; ≤10 bullets).
- **S** — stack (repo root, runtime, pkg mgr, test cmd—known facts only).
- **!** — blockers / failures / unknowns.
- **→** — next 1–3 steps.

Abbreviate paths (`src/...`). Symbols/arrows OK. No repetition of this rule file.
